{
  "texts": [
    "Paula brings forth how Gaby is for Paula within their social system 'project group.'",
    "Paula used her own body to make her absent group members overtly present in distinct and observable ways.",
    "She reevoked past encounters with her group members during aninterview situation, using human presencing to bring herself forth as the group leader.",
    "Her presencing of the others played out through a moment-to-moment unfolding of her own doing and sayings.",
    "These can be traced to the interplay of bodily dynamics where subtle events in the pico-scale and micro-scale of bodily real-time activity, such as shifts in gaze and prosody, gave rise to the envoicing of absent group members."
  ]
}